# Project Overview & Coding Standards

## Tech Stack
- Language: TypeScript 5.x (strict mode)
- Runtime: Node.js 20 LTS
- Framework: [YOUR_FRAMEWORK e.g. NestJS / Next.js 14 / Express]
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 with Prisma ORM
- Testing: Vitest + Playwright (E2E)
- CI/CD: GitLab CI
- Container: Docker + Kubernetes
- Infrastructure: Terraform on Azure

## Architecture
- Monorepo with Turborepo
- Domain-driven folder structure: `src/{domain}/{feature}/`
- Shared packages in `packages/`
- All API endpoints follow RESTful conventions

## Coding Standards
- Prefer functional programming; avoid classes unless framework requires them
- Use early returns for guard clauses
- All functions must have explicit return types
- All errors must be typed and specific — never `catch(e: any)`
- Comments in English only
- Max function length: 40 lines — extract if longer
- No `console.log` in production code — use structured logger

## Naming Conventions
- Files: kebab-case (`user-service.ts`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase
- Types/interfaces: PascalCase with `I` prefix for interfaces (`IUserRepository`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Database columns: snake_case

## Git
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`
- Branch naming: `feature/TICKET-123-short-description`
- All PRs require passing CI + 1 review
